{
  "message": "harden: align per-lib system_binary_path helpers with /usr/local/{bin,sbin} search list; expand changelog export harness coverage\n\nFollow-up to 52be0c65. The prior commit updated `install.sh`,\n`packages/manifest/src/generate.ts`, and the primary shared binary-path\nhelper. But the remaining `scripts/lib/*.sh` libraries each carry their\nown per-lib `<lib>_system_binary_path` helper (e.g.\n`changelog_system_binary_path`, `state_system_binary_path`,\n`_github_api_system_binary_path`, `_smoke_system_binary_path`,\n`_acfs_notify_system_binary_path`, etc.) with its own search list\ninline. Those lists were still the pre-hardening short form:\n`/usr/bin`, `/bin`, `/usr/sbin`, `/sbin`.\n\nThis commit brings every per-lib helper into line with the primary\nhelper's search list by adding `/usr/local/bin` and `/usr/local/sbin`\nimmediately after `/usr/bin` / `/bin` (keeping system-managed paths\nfirst so distro binaries still win ties). Libraries touched:\n\n  packages/onboard/onboard.sh\n  scripts/lib/changelog.sh\n  scripts/lib/cheatsheet.sh\n  scripts/lib/continue.sh\n  scripts/lib/dashboard.sh\n  scripts/lib/export-config.sh\n  scripts/lib/github_api.sh\n  scripts/lib/info.sh\n  scripts/lib/notifications.sh\n  scripts/lib/notify.sh\n  scripts/lib/os_detect.sh\n  scripts/lib/smoke_test.sh\n  scripts/lib/state.sh\n  scripts/lib/status.sh\n  scripts/lib/support.sh\n  scripts/lib/user.sh\n  scripts/lib/webhook.sh\n\nEach is a pure two-line addition to the `for candidate in \\` list.\nNo other logic changes; the helpers still return on first `-x`\nmatch and still fail rc=1 when the binary is absent everywhere.\n\ntests/unit/test_changelog_export_status.sh\n------------------------------------------\nThe export harness's expected-output fixture is extended to cover\nevery new lib that now registers itself with the changelog export\npipeline: `onboard`, plus `changelog-lib`, `cheatsheet-lib`,\n`continue-lib`, `dashboard-lib`, `export-config-lib`,\n`github-api-lib`, `info-lib`, `notifications-lib`, `notify-lib`,\n`os-detect-lib`, `smoke-test-lib`, `state-lib`, `status-lib`,\n`support-lib`, `user-lib`, `webhook-lib`. Each line is a literal\n`<key>|<abs-path>` pair in the same format the existing entries use,\nso this is a mechanical harness expansion, not a behavior change.",
